function err = probiterr(b,optoride)% given an estimate of b and model specified by probitoption (global), this% function returns the error. yobs are the observed vals.  data is a global% design matrix: col1-1's col2-coregressor(coh) col3-main regressor (time)% see probitf.m% Determine the particular verions of the probit and hence the% interpretation of the regressor vector, b, using either the global% variable, probitoption, or by calling with a second arguement:%  probiterr(b,optoride) will overide the gobal variable probitoptionglobal probitoption global probitdf data yobs yerrif nargin>1  y = probitf(b,data,optoride);else  y = probitf(b,data);end% err = sum((y-yobs).^2);err = -sum(log(normpdf(yobs,y,yerr)));